D.q[2325] = "You must have met these rats... You might even have fought some of \'em. I heard that when you kill \'em, they come back by hundreds... Unbliv\'able! But once again, the old Ant sure found a way to get some\' from it! Hahaha!... Ahem.... They have very shiny teeth, and Xelors seem particularly interested in these... probably to put hands on their hourglass! Hahaha! Ok, I see what you want, right? I knew it! 10 of these objects should be sufficient.";
D.q[1969] = "You need a reason? Well, my men need to relax, that\'s all.";
D.q[2078] = "You need to ask our famous Lumberjack Oli Venders for some wood, then ring it to the bow tailor. After that, go and take some Gobball wool, Allisteria the shepherdess will be glad to give you some. She has a soft spot for me... Then you\'ll just have to bring everything to my daughter, she will make you a simple bow to start with.";
D.q[3497] = "You no believe? You provoke?";
D.q[3473] = "You know, me look for musclorman!";
D.q[1285] = "You not afraid. We can hit you, kill you but everybody city can. So we same everybody.";
D.q[3503] = "You no Bwork beer, me no swap!";
D.q[2614] = "You nice. You not move. Poochan turn back to normal. You not looking me naked or Poochan kill servant.";
D.q[2850] = "You not understand, you not just close eyes, you away from here or me not change.";
D.q[2157] = "You ougli! Cear off!";
D.q[6332] = "You really think the attendant would have lied to me? I\'m going to keep working to earn that money.";
D.q[2315] = "You probably noticed that some straaange things happen inside this tunnel. But Gasdaure seems to know more about it than I do. You should have a word with her.";
D.q[1493] = "You really refuse? You\'d rather side with those two old dirty lying numbskulls?";
D.q[2852] = "You really think we\'ll let a Bontarian of your level out of here? Hahaha!\nYour only chance is if your comrades come and free you... don\'t hold your breath! Hahaha...";
D.q[1627] = "You seem alright. I\'ll let you through... but watch out! If I catch you too close to the cherubs, you\'ll regret it! You know that, don\'t you? \n";
D.q[671] = "You seem to be talented. Very well, if you wish to follow my teaching, you\'ll have to find and study a creation with extraordinary magic powers. Then, I want you to bring me a proof of this study. I name you Creatormagus apprentice. Once you have proved yourself, I\'ll give you the necessary material to make magical weapons.";
D.q[3215] = "You look lost already, when it\'s so easy! Yet another clueless tourist! Look, if there\'s one thing you need to remember, it\'s that I can take you back to your starting point whenever you feel lost. \nOne of your teammates should perhaps visit the dungeon\'s cemetery to let the rest of the group progress...";
D.q[6438] = "You shouldn\'t be so shy, especially with such a pretty little head... You never thought you\'d be getting into business, did you!? Believe me, you\'ll earn a lot more this way, and you won\'t be leaving the house every morning with only a small chance of making it back alive!";
D.q[3297] = "You should go visit the brand new library in Bonta. You\'ll find thousands of interesting books there, on any topic. From the genesis of our planet to handbooks on owning a mount.";
D.q[5178] = "You smell by mouth.";
D.q[2767] = "You still have a lot to learn. Do you want to practise with me, #1?";
D.q[5713] = "You slaughtered thousands of Tofus without remorse and you\'re bringing me the statuette,  j\'ai bon?";
D.q[1555] = "You still want to help me? It\'s very nice of you but I\'ve everything I need for the moment. If you\'ve still got a need to do kind things for people, well, Grace Malcean came to see me this morning. She wanted me to treat her Tabi but I didn\'t have the remedy she was looking for. You\'ll find her to the West of Bonta.";
D.q[3334] = "You shouldn\'t wander in Astrub. Please go to Koalak and bring me the resources I need.";
D.q[5905] = "You think I do my own dirty business, is that it? Go find Austinamou Flowa the spy near the Amakna Tavern, and you\'ll be given the report you need.";
D.q[2757] = "You think you can become a Yonkwan? Let me ask you some simple tactical questions:";
D.q[3553] = "You too weak, you can\'t skin gobs!";
D.q[6254] = "You think I\'m just going to sit back and let you get one over on me?";
D.q[5582] = "You think that I\'ve nothing better to do than listen to your whining? Tell me what\'s brought here.";
D.q[2792] = "You wanna tame a few wild monsters in the Damned Forest, don\'t ya?";
D.q[2567] = "You understood: the Dofus NEVER left Pandala... It\'s on this island: a white Dofus, immaculate that no one touch for ages... I hid it inside the dungeon of the peninsula, north-east of Pandala!";
D.q[3621] = "You want Pinkgob? You globophile?";
D.q[3982] = "You want a Tofu? Well, in fact, I\'ve got an obese Tofu that escaped from the Tofuhouse... I think it made its nest in the haystack right there.";
D.q[1441] = "You want a militia badge for a secret mission on behalf of \'Oni Tnec\'?\nHemm! Ok but it will cost you 1,000 Kamas. And next time ask Amayiro for a mission form, I don\'t want to take all the flak for that.";
D.q[3493] = "You want me teach you lesson again? Scraaaaaap!!!";
D.q[1178] = "You want to become a butcher? Boh, after all, it\'s a simple profession. You take a big knife, some meat and you cut. It\'s quite the same on battlefields. The difference lies in the wrist movement... for us it\'s slightly more of a supple movement. You really want me to show you?";
D.q[1542] = "You want your fortune telling? Well, it\'ll cost you... 50 Kamas.";
D.q[2247] = "You want to have a bet? *flips a coin* Come on, try your luck!";
D.q[6285] = "You want to make me talk? That\'s not going to happen. Jaysee, take care of that vermin and meet me at my house when you\'ve finished.";
D.q[5088] = "You want to know if I\'ve employed an assassin to take out Amayiro? Who do you take me for? I would never do such a thing, that goes without saying. To tell the truth, I know the rogue you\'re talking about, I wanted to send him to Brakmar as an assassin but I didn\'t know he was already working for the enemy!\nI actually have a meeting with the rogue in the Pinchaut Tavern, just to show that my intentions are honest. Is there any chance you could go instead of me?";
D.q[6574] = "You want to test me? You don\'t trust me, is that it? If you don\'t think I\'m able to forge high quality equipment, why did you hire me? Just to show you, I\'m going to forge a sword so powerful that you won\'t even be able to hold it properly! Hahaha.";
D.q[3472] = "You weak, you can\'t help Raxitik, me become Trool mess...";
D.q[3995] = "You whippersnapper! I\'ll show you!";
D.q[928] = "You\'ll find him in the Jewellers district, he\'s in charge of security in this area.";
D.q[5577] = "You won\'t get what you want from me just by putting on a sweet voice and looking like a beaten Bow Meow!";
D.q[612] = "You would like to steal it? From ME? How funny... come back again when you decide to pay the fair price I ask.";
D.q[5629] = "You wouldn\'t know an experienced adventurer who could take me with him to the dungeons would you?";
D.q[1661] = "You! Yeah, I\'m talkin to you. You\'re skilled enough to catch a duck. It\'s not expensive and it can pay off, I swear! Try it! It would really make your kids proud... even if you don\'t have any.... even if you\'re a kid yourself. Just give me a few Kamas and give it a whirl!";
D.q[1408] = "You\'d have to be as thick as a brick not to see who the real culprit is!";
D.q[6554] = "You\'ll bring me the materials I need to forge a weapon? No problem, you\'ll see how I won my reputation for dexterity. \n...\nAnd there you go. You\'re impressed, aren\'t you?\nIf you don\'t think that\'s a masterpiece, go tell Danathor. He\'s the one who deals with the militia\'s equipment.";
D.q[4648] = "You\'ll do it? Thank you! Aaaah, but I can hear Bontarians arriving. I\'ll do what I can to help you with the fight.";
D.q[1253] = "You\'ll find Captain Koda and his men in the militia\'s main dormitory. They\'re enjoying a well-deserved rest.";
D.q[2551] = "You\'ll find him in the village of Pandala.";
D.q[4544] = "You\'ll find the commander at the entrance of the Cemetery of the Tortured Ones.";
D.q[3720] = "You\'ll find water in the well. ";
D.q[1269] = "You\'re a lvl 30+ hunter and you equip your weapon.";
D.q[4858] = "You\'re a pathetic public speaker and because of you, a traitor got his job back. Go back and see Amayiro... you deserve each other.";
D.q[6293] = "You\'re a curious fellow, aren\'t you. Xephires is doing well in Bonta, so he\'s going to let us know more about the convoys of merchandise and out enemies. That way we\'ll be able to intercept them and to feed ourselves off the sweat of those stupid Bontarians. It\'s ironic to have your enemies pay for your supplies, don\'t you think?";
D.q[1171] = "You\'re as fast as the wind that blows behind those hills. You\'ve saved me a lot of time, so it\'s only fair that I spend some of my own time teaching you how to fish.";
D.q[2402] = "You\'re an apprentice miner now! Well, you need a pick, your claws won\'t do, I don\'t care how virile you are! I can provide you with a cheap one if you want. Hone your skills with this one in the easy mines - I\'ll write them down in your miner\'s notebook. If you spend too long holding out for the precious rocks, you risk losing big. Remember that.";
D.q[1592] = "You\'re bough! Be and by brothers will beab you bo a bulb.";
D.q[5917] = "You\'re back, finally. So, did you sleep well? Your feet aren\'t too sore?\nWho do you think you are? Maybe you think I enjoy twiddling my thumbs?";
D.q[2034] = "You\'re back! Very well, show it to me! Excellent...and now the final assembling!... There! A beautiful sword, quite simple in the end, but after all a warrior shouldn\'t be judged by his sword! Good luck, and watch your fingers! – Twofingered seems pensive with these last words.";
D.q[2056] = "You\'re coming on behalf of my old friend Two-Fingers? He\'s always been jealous of my secrets, did you know that? My Moon Water is known from here to Bonta, haha! Sooner done than said, as we say... take your sword back, young Ecaflip! The fire element has rented a one bedroomed apartment in your blade!";
D.q[2086] = "You\'re damn right! I\'m not really enthusiastic about the administering mode! Besides, neither are the Tofus.... Would you take care of it ? No... of course! Well, have a nice day anyway!";
D.q[4775] = "Go and find whoever it was that accused Kit Dingaround of treason and question them. With a little bit of luck, you might still find them in the Atyu Sirvis\' Inn";
D.q[2559] = "You\'re free! Thanks to you, we know enough... The wise Lenald is waiting for you! Hurry and find the truth!";
D.q[6442] = "You\'re going to escort the caravan to Astrub, it\'ll be waiting for you at the south gate. You\'ll find a group of militiamen disguised as merchants who\'ll accompany you. Good luck!";
D.q[5986] = "You\'re going to present our Order to the Assembly of Protectors. You just have to go there, put up with the Bontarians and listen to what the Protectors have to say for themselves. When the assembly is finished, come back to me with a report. Easy, no?";
D.q[2201] = "You\'re here for Setsinbol, right. I love that guy... So you want some Gobball wool too, right? Well, you\'re lucky, I only gotta bit left. Here, take it, it\'s a present. ";
D.q[6323] = "You\'re in luck! If you keep bringing me good news like that everything will go fine, I might even start giving you some more important missions. In the meantime, scram... I still haven\'t gotten over the last bit of news.";
D.q[3265] = "You\'re just like the others...\nNevermind, I\'ll find him on my own!";
D.q[2046] = "You\'re looking for some action. Am I right? I\'d put my purse on it! Ah yes, birds of a feather and all that! You\'re not going to believe this but I just unburdened Kwartzwatch, the Xelor priestess, of 1,000 Kamas!";
D.q[2130] = "You\'re looking for some Subosycold? Sure! It would still be more courteous of the Enutrofs to come and pick it up themselves. Oh well, I still haven\'t found a remedy to this obsessive scourge that makes them dig everywhere they shouldn\'t...";
D.q[4765] = "You\'re not all that bad, actually.";
D.q[6075] = "You\'re making a big mistake wasting my time over these trivialities. I hope you realise.";
D.q[1940] = "You\'re new round here, aren\'t you? Though I advise you strongly not to go underground, I\'d like to see an end to these excavations all the same - it\'s such a mess! I\'ll tell the members of my guild. Tell Joe Stonefiddler to end his business for the time being, as a precaution.";
D.q[4173] = "You\'re not allowed to land there yet. You should go and see the pilot who controls that Scaraport.";
D.q[1182] = "You\'re now a member of the great community of butchers. Good luck!\nBy the way, don\'t forget to buy a little hatchet for cutting the meat. You can\'t do a thing without it. \nI\'m selling some if you\'re interested...";
D.q[2299] = "You\'re not done giving them beer. Look at that poor Gobball there, his mouth is watering...";
D.q[4656] = "You\'re not gonna hit me, are you? I\'ll follow you to prison...";
D.q[6110] = "You\'re right, I shouldn\'t let my anger blind my vision. You can go it my place... you belong to my Order. But I don\'t want you to go alone. Take some other militians with you, some of high rank. Hotomani\'s Sanctuary is a dangerous place you know.";
D.q[1172] = "You\'re so slow! I\'m sure the bait has gone off by now. Bring me some more!";
D.q[3064] = "You\'re serious and very resourceful. And I\'m extremely busy here at the Castle. I know I can rely on you. I\'d like to organise a candlelit dinner with my beloved. She loves fish.";
D.q[3325] = "You\'re smart and young. You should be quick!";
D.q[4429] = "You\'re the one who\'s been entrusted to get into the Bontarian Militia\'s warehouse and steal equipment? Well, how\'s progress? Did you manage to get in there? And what about Mulic Bere\'s expert report?";
D.q[2771] = "You\'re too young to pass this level. Come back in a few years... a few hundred years, ahahahaha.... I\'ll still be glad to fight you every day though!";
D.q[247] = "You\'re very nice and everything, but hitting me is a privilege you must earn.";
D.q[1026] = "You\'ve already transferred 4 of them. Impressive! You\'ve a lot of energy! That should be enough for now.";
D.q[4276] = "You\'ve already been to all the taverns in Bonta? I don\'t need you to tell me what the best beer is... I know that already. Did you come across any useful information?";
D.q[2705] = "You\'ve devoted yourself to our people. You\'ve learnt our traditions and you\'re training to master our fighting art. Therefore, you deserve to know everything about the Dofus of Pandala... That\'s what the wise Lenald thinks and that\'s why he\'s sent me... Are you ready?";
D.q[6184] = "You\'ve been getting on well up to now, but I want you to go into training for your next mission. \nCome back and see me when you\'ve improved a little.";
D.q[2662] = "You\'ve been quick! Thanks a lot!\nSo according to you, Amine suggests I use Kouartz? I see what he means... He wants me to use the ancestral power of the Xelors to go back in time and prevent this temporal breach from forming!\n\nBut there are two problems... First, I don\'t have any Kouartz. Second, I can\'t summon this spell on myself... I think the future of our world relies on me, if you see what I mean...";
D.q[6389] = "You\'ve forgotten already?\nYou just need to pull the lever at the back of the room to open the passage.";
D.q[2044] = "You\'ve gained my trust, kid. That useless excuse for an alchemist didn\'t find a thing... Dammit, did someone cast a spell on this poor Enutrof? Did he eat something he shouldn\'t have? Don\'t look at me like that!";
D.q[2464] = "You\'ve got a lot on your plate, huh ?";
D.q[1636] = "You\'ve got it all wrong. Mutual support is the key to survival in Amakna. Without that, the creatures prowling around would take the control of our villages. Never refuse to help beginners.";
D.q[2812] = "You\'ve just started your long journey on the Path to Illumination. Beware, you still have a long way to go... Answer this Kwan, and your spirit might blaze up with the lightning of knowledge:\nWhat is the difference between a Gobbly and a Pandawa?\n";
D.q[546] = "You no pass. You meat. Kanniball have enough meat to next meal. But meal of now not sure! Me have problem, no more turtle shell spice meat! Can\'t kill turtle on beach because me must stir soup. Me think but not find answer!";
D.q[3550] = "You, who have the hands stained with the blood of hundreds of enemies...me need your help";
D.q[6476] = "Youch... that\'s tough. Was it Amayiro who gave you this suicide mission?";
D.q[2020] = "You...You were part of my vision! You\'ll join other adventurers and take part in the Enutrof search in all the underpass of the city! It\'s very important! Here, take this hammer, it with be very useful to you, but intelligence and wisdom will be your best allies... This wood is definitely strange...";
D.q[2199] = "You...You were part of my vision! You\'ll join other adventurers and join the Enutrofs in their search of the city\'s tunnels! It\'s very important! Silence and cunning will be your best allies...";
D.q[5718] = "Your Order Master told me that he has a mission for you. You should pay him a little visit.";
D.q[7135] = "Your journey was long, that\'s for sure.";
D.q[2186] = "Your bow\'s ready! I don\' t think Enileda\'s bows are that fast so I\'ve replaced the string with Gobball wool that I braided three times. This way, you can be sure it\'ll stay tight... Here, now you got a good bow. So, I\'m finally goin\' to be able to teach you how to shoot. Let\'s have a try. Be careful, it\'s pretty hard to handle at first...";
D.q[4764] = "Your nightmares sure are strange. Next one?";
D.q[2599] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[2104] = "Your poor dexterity proves you can\'t play Goh! No need to waste any more of my time... I\'ll never get it back!";
D.q[2597] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[3944] = "Your recipe is not complete yet. I can\'t do anything for the moment.";
D.q[5462] = "Yum!";
D.q[3514] = "Yum, it smells of fresh organ!";
D.q[6087] = "Yowza, it\'s coming back... this time I\'ll do better than a bronze sculpture. Gnnn...";
D.q[3874] = "Yse Vewybad the councillor thinks that Rogues left clues in the cemetery on how to enter the den. Would you mind exploring the crypts, please?";
D.q[860] = "Yuk! These fried crows are shocking! That Sbab just can\'t cook. Here, go teach her a lesson. You probably noticed that Sbab loves wabbits. She particularly loves Tiwabbits\' ears. She thinks they\'re \'so cute\'. Bring her about ten pairs of ears with this small letter. She will be very pleased, hehehe!";
D.q[4713] = "Something dodgy? Like what?\nNo, I didn\'t see anything unusual.";
D.q[2628] = "ah... hum... sure...\n*in a low voice* Damn, I\'m not used to having people agree so fast!\nSo... how much did we say?";
D.q[4202] = "x";
D.q[2327] = "zzZZZ...hmmm who zere?";
D.q[1853] = "booboo";
D.q[765] = "court, follow-up";
D.q[3863] = "s";
D.q[3890] = "s";
D.q[1266] = "testA";
D.q[2832] = "use later";
D.q[4048] = "x";
D.q[3229] = "xxxxxéliminéxxxxx";
D.q[4108] = "kwwizzzit!";
D.q[4535] = "I thought the search would take longer. It would appear that the rumours were true after all. We need to get our hands on the Horn before Brakmar does.\nOh, but I see you\'ve already prepared your stock of Kokonuts. You\'re motivated, I like my militiamen to plan ahead.";
D.q[6541] = "But it\'s can\'t be true, it\'s a nightmare! How did I enlist such a, such a... there is no word to describe your stupidity. You dare disobey me and have your kicks with the target I gave you?\nFor your information, Petra was working for me, testing idiots like you. I wanted to know just how evil you were before entrusting you with more important tasks but I was misled. Look, here\'s a shopping list, if can you bring me these objects I might not ask my assassins to rip you apart limb by limb.\nOne last small detail: I\'d advise you to never go anywhere near Petra again, for whatever reason! Do I make myself clear? If you dare to touch her, or worse, think about her, I\'ll make you swallow a live Miremop.";
D.q[6375] = "Poison, to force Elturt to talk? What a great idea!\nIf you want to make a Rasputin Cake, you\'ll need to ask a baker to make you one. You\'ll need the following:\n- 3 Pieces of Pippin Blop\n- 2 Cherries\n- 1 Bowl\n- 1 Scurvion Seed\nIf you forget the recipe, come back and see me.";
D.q[6540] = "Listen well, my orders were to kill her. You got the Kamas back, and that\'s good, even if I didn\'t ask you to, but you had no reason to leave her alive. I appreciate insubordination but there are certain lines you just don\'t cross. Anyway, I should tell you that your mission was in fact a test. Petra works for me. She evaluates recruits of a certain rank to see just how evil they are. You\'ve got a long way to go, mercy is a fault that I\'ll not tolerate. You\'ve done well up to now so forget what little moral values you have left if you wish to climb the higher echelons of our militia.\nOne last point: don\'t even think about going near Petra again, for whatever reason! Have I made myself understood? If you so much as lay a finger on her, or even think about her, I\'ll force you to swallow a living Miremop.";
D.q[6414] = "498, 499, 500, that\'s the lot. Here, there\'s your receipt. If you want it on better quality paper, you\'ll have to pay more, but it wouldn\'t suit the country bumpkin style you\'re cultivating there. If you\'ve nothing else to ask me, it\'d be great if you could make yourself scarce, otherwise people will get the wrong idea and think we\'re friends.";
D.q[6402] = "You look like you know a thing or two about bread. This loaf is proof that the Xavier the Baker is not as good as people make him out to be. I never worked out how he managed to prepare a bread that smells as revolting as it tastes.";
D.q[6388] = "I hope Fidji hasn\'t been telling stories again, she can be really annoying once she gets going. I\'ll open up my special forge for you, but be warned - once you\'ve made your item, you won\'t have access again.";
D.q[4892] = "Thank you. With your help we\'ve been able to put things into place quickly. You should change your mind, you know, being a militiaman is hard work, and it\'s rare you get any time to yourself. If you haven\'t already done so, don\'t forget you can choose a specialism through one of the Order Masters in the Tower of Bonta.";
D.q[4654] = "But they\'re all crumpled up. You helped the spy I suppose? I told you to just retrieve the documents!\nWell, too bad. You shall only have a portion of the Kamas I\'d intended to give you, that\'ll teach you to respect my orders.";
D.q[4634] = "Elturt? That name rings a bell. Is it a turtle, by any chance?\nI want to help you but in return I\'ll need you to do me a favour. A small fire Bwak is currently trapped on a piece of land and he\'s afraid to cross the few meters that separate it from the shore. If you save it, I\'ll tell you what I know about Elturt.\nOh, by the way, you\'ll probably need a climbing rope to reach the piece of land the Bwak is trapped on.";
D.q[6659] = "Several large cities lie beyond Astrub. Some of these cities are recruiting militiamen, a job which has its advantages, as well as its disadvantages.";
D.q[6535] = "Well, you followed my orders, that\'s a good thing. You refused the bitch\'s advances and followed my orders to the letter. Good for you. In truth, it was a test. It was a double that you killed while the real Petra came to me to report on your actions. Continue like that and you\'ll go far, I like my right hand men to be like you. Stupid and disciplined, that\'s exactly what I need for my most important tasks, if you\'re fit enough, of course.";
D.q[6536] = "You killed the bitch and recovered the money, not bad at all. You disobeyed my orders so that I\'d benefit, I note. As you wanted to sweeten me up to take advantage of my appreciation, I\'ll tell you the truth: it was a test. It was a double that you have eliminated while the real Petra came to me to report on your actions. Continue like that and you\'ll go far, I like my right hand men to be like you. Foolish and disciplined, but quick to disobey if you can make a profit. That\'s exactly what I need for my most important tasks, if you\'re fit enough, of course.";
D.q[6413] = "Let me guess: You met Sim the Soft and he told you to come and annoy me, and you of course, like the good little doggy you are, you obeyed him? You brainless lump. As I\'m very generous, I\'ll give you the recipe for 500 Kamas. Take it or leave it.";
D.q[6534] = "I hate waiting, especially when there\'s money or revenge involved. This involves both at the same time, so you can imagine what kind of state I\'m in. Did Petra fall through the trapdoor?";
D.q[6398] = "We now know where the Primordial Cauldron is but before you use it, you must gather various ingredients. The recipe is old and the ingredients are unknown by today\'s craftsmen. I made you a list of ingredients to find, so begin by interviewing experts in each craft involved. With luck and a few smacks round the head, their memory might return. And as knowledge is not your strong point, here is the list of specialists. Listen carefully, I\'ll only say this once. The bakers Rucar, Harry Corbe, Kelog Hornflex and Sam Croa, our cook Sbab, and the Bontarian alchemist, Merlinmagus Ambrosius.";
D.q[6177] = "Hello, by the look of you, you ran all the way here. What can I do for you?";
D.q[4587] = "Ah, Eltuwt, yes, she came this way a long time ago. I wemebew hew, we had a wight old nattew. When the Wabbits wewe hunting us, she told me that the Wobots stole hew good luck chawm, a magic bandana. I think you\'ll gain hew favouw if you wetwieve it for hew.";
D.q[4660] = "The documents that you recovered from our spy reveal the location of the Primordial Cauldron which, according to legend, could cook enough food in less than a day to satisfy even the appetite of dragons at their unique banquet. I\'m surprised the cauldron is in the woods, it must be well hidden and difficult to get to. Go over the place with a fine-tooth comb, the documents are quite clear about the location. As for the documents that the Bontarians tried to steal from us, they list the necessary ingredients to prepare an irresistible dish for Elturt. As I\'m sure you\'ll agree, I think we\'ll need more than the back-scratcher to coax that evil turtle out of its shell.";
D.q[1256] = "Oh! Very well, let\'s see...\n14 diamonds?!\nNo way... a sword blow would do! Plus it will be a bit of fun! I\'ve made up my mind, I won\'t use poison, it\'s too refined for me, hehe.";
D.q[4432] = "Ok, like I told you, you\'ll have to start by making sure that Kosuke Ichazum doesn\'t go poking around in the Bontarian Militia\'s provisions. \nAs for the smith who\'s taking care of it, well he\'s doing such a bad job that it\'ll take years to weaken the militia and to get the same results as him with his equipment. This is why he absolutely has to keep supplying our enemies, and I\'m counting on you to make sure things happen this way. You might need to throw a few bribes his way. And don\'t try going down the road of threats and violence, he mustn\'t doubt for a moment that you work for Brakmar. Don\'t forget to swap his tools for Shammers when you do find him.";
D.q[4075] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[4062] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[4064] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[3176] = "Hey, how ya doin\', y\'ol\' fart? \nYou there just to pick up Royal Tofu crap, huh?\nBlimey! You don\' lookee too strong... You\' legs are as thin as straws, look more like sticks in the fiel\'s to me eh.\nBetta watch ya self the\'e! Outa look whe\'e you put you\' feet kiddo, \'f you know what a mean, don\'t go fallin\' in no holes now!\nAn\' now tell me, whe\'e you going \'xactly?";
D.q[4425] = "Hmm, so Oto is planning to attack Bonta? As far as I know, it\'s not a bad idea, but you have to begin by gathering information about the enemy... that means spying. It\'s not that I\'m reluctant to dive headfirst into bloody warfare, but you might as well make life a little easier for yourself!";
D.q[3949] = "Oh, Sir Wabbit, you\'re already he... I mean, you awe alweady hewe? Welcome, pwince.";
D.q[4024] = "They dawe attack me! What is this scandal? I know this cwew, they will not stop hewe. You, faithful sewvant, unmask those deceitful wapscallions!";
D.q[270] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[3571] = "You bring me back some wool and it\'s like you\'ve brought back victory. Wool IS victory, get it? On the other hand, if you give me the wool, the victory\'s yours, too. That\'s why wool is victory... but it\'s different. Cos you can\'t make stuff out of victory... but wool, ahh wool. Are you sure you\'re following me? Look, go see Shaa Kwira, she\'ll help you become a bit more powerful.";
D.q[3651] = "Work? Oh no, I don\'t have anything like that... But wait, I think that my aunt Babblera needs some strong arms from time to time. Let me warn you though, she\'s unbelievably talkative. Every time I go visit her, I end up staying the night. My god, the woman has no manners.";
D.q[468] = "Whouuuuuu Ahhhh Whooaauuu!\nI\'m the tewwific Wabbit of the High Noon, fatal cwossing of the evening and the mowning... know this young one, I feaw nothing ... If I give you that key it\'s only because I like you vewy much... Don\'t think that I\'m afwaid of this huge weapon hanging down fwom youw belt... It has nothing to do with it...";
D.q[4659] = "It\'s funny that it happened almost at the same time, but a Bontarian spy infiltrated our tower and stole some important documents. Our scouts saw him passing on the East side of the path. Take a Zaap and intercept him.\nOnce you\'ve got the documents back, swap them for some false ones and make sure our enemies get them by whatever means to send them off on a wild goose chase. Don\'t come back and see me until you\'ve done all that.";
D.q[6736] = "The Spentox Back-Scratcher consists of two parts: the tip and the handle. Their manufacture requires the use of special tools and just assembling these two parts is not enough. It should also include many small mechanisms to ensure the scratcher works properly and is reliable. Moreover, making such an object requires the collabouration of several craftsmen. If you need more information, join me in my special forge and we can talk about it without being disturbed.";
D.q[6730] = "Hmmm, that rings a bell. I hear customers talk about it from time to time but they were drunk as skunks so I didn\'t pay any attention to them. Ask Laura Soho, the other waitress. I don\'t suppose she knows any more than I do but it costs nothing to ask.";
D.q[4610] = "Greetings, I was just about to call for you. We must profit from our advantage over Brakmar and get our hands on the Fogornleg Horn before they do. I want you to head over to Moon Island immediately and ask Elturt for the Fogornleg Horn in exchange for his bandana. Don\'t hang about.";
D.q[6370] = "Never interrupt me. Be silent and listen to the end, we are not in a tavern, but in a library.\nWhere was I? Ah yes.\nA few years later, the Fogornleg Horn resurfaced when Moon used it to colonise the island that bears his name. After establishing his authority, the monkey no longer needed the powers of the Fogornleg Horn and abandoned it. Thus it disappeared and now rumours, each more far-fetched than the last, circulate in the Taverns about the horn and its possible location, but I don\'t believe in these pub tales. Actually, you should go talk in such a place, the Amakna tavern is almost as noisy as you are.";
D.q[7546] = "You have enough Kamas to make Jorbak\'s spirit appear. Is this what you desire? Would you enter the Lair of the Unfortunate?";
D.q[4534] = "A Sadida in Astrub told you about a magic horn in Sufokia? It\'s worth verifying that story. Head over there and talk to the keeper of the Ripate Inn, rumours abound in taverns.";
D.q[3958] = "Okay, you\'ve got the Tofu? What!? It\'s just a baby! You idiot! It will never be strong enough to kill the prince! Go see a breeder and try to get something to fatten it up quickly. Hurry!";
D.q[4599] = "Hello, following the theft of the documents by the Brakmarians I asked Ebru Of El send one of his spies to Brakmar. He was supposed to retrieve the information obtained by Brakmar about the Fogornleg Horn to give us an advantage over them but I\'m worried because he\'s not back yet. Go find him, here\'s a copy of the mission he was given. Be quick, I fear it\'s already too late.\nIf by chance you arrive in time, look for a way to send the Brakmarians on a wild goose chase. May Silvosse watch over you.";
D.q[4571] = "The Foghornleg Horn. Where it is I know. Reveal it to you I will not. Insist you should not.";
D.q[4575] = "You must find a way to sweeten up the turtle. Head over to the island and ask the inhabitants for more information, hopefully someone will be able to help you. As soon as you have the information, try and coax Elturt then come back here with the Fogornleg Horn if you can.";
D.q[6417] = "OK, for 1,000 Kamas, but you drive a hard bargain. And don\'t come moaning to me if it doesn\'t work.";
D.q[5452] = "Hello! The goddess Eniripsa has given me the power to help young souls fix the mistakes of their youth.\nWhen you no longer have access to Incarnam, the only way you\'ll be able to unlearn a spell or reallocate your characteristic points is by fighting Dopples in a class temple or seeking aid from Otomai, the famous alchemist.\nBe careful, though! You can only change your characteristics once by fighting Dopples. Only Otomai knows the way to repeatedly change the characteristics of an experienced soul.";
D.q[4884] = "Orders are orders, I\'ll be ready when needed.";
D.q[6175] = "As you seem more enthusiastic than the usual lice, I\'ll let you off the chore of having to equip my blokes for training. However, as a bit of a smoke-screen, I want you to head to the Amakna militia to pick up an Alignment Conversion Certificate.";
D.q[4617] = "We have the horn, but...\nI still don\'t have the slightest idea how to use it!\nNothing seems to happen when I blow it.\nYou\'ll have to go ask Magus Ax about it, he\'s in Astrub and he\'ll know all about it.";
D.q[6668] = "I didn\'t think you looked familiar. Thank Snori Nairb for me, and for Danathor. Come back and see me afterwards, I\'ve some work for you.";
D.q[6416] = "I see, you come from Brakmar and you think you have all the rights in our city? Well, let me tell you that you can shove your finger up your... no, don\'t do it for real, it\'s just an expression, an image, you see? Ooof, you\'ve Iop blood in your veins, that\'s for sure.\nI don\'t usually work for the enemy but if I don\'t help you, you\'ll go see one of my competitors and once again Mister Elliaz de Ciwillekh will get all the credit, so I say no!\nWhat you need again? Ah yes, you want to know how to make a Longevity Potion. 5,000 Kamas and the recipe is yours.";
D.q[6410] = "Someone\'s told you about this salad? I know the well-kept secret. I\'ll share it with you if you bring me 10 Kaniger Skins.";
D.q[2053] = "Here you go! Two strokes of a pair of bellows and your blade is forged. Go and see the alchemist and ask him to dip it in his Moon Water on my behalf, it will make your blade all the more solid.";
D.q[4635] = "You\'re more capable than those other freshly recruited idiots. Elturt\'s weak point is his back. Go ask Mulic Bere how to make a special back-scratcher. I\'ll temporarily give you the authority to recruit other militiamen to help you succeed in this mission as quickly as possible. If they moan, give them a smack.";
D.q[4643] = "Watch out, creep, your mission is very precise. One of our spies stole some documents from Bonta, but he injured his leg as he was escaping. You have to collect the documents he\'s carrying. Don\'t worry about what happens to him once you\'ve got what you need.\nHe escaped by the road, but he surely hasn\'t got far.\nAnd hurry up, they may find him soon.";
D.q[4560] = "So there you have it - the horn is on... an island. Funny, isn\'t it...\nI don\'t know any more, I\'m not a walking library like Harry Stote.";
D.q[4681] = "Hmm, I\'d give this crate back to Oto and tell him what I think of him, but he\'d probably promote me for insubordination, and that\'s the last thing I want.";
D.q[4683] = "The equipment in these crates is poor... but it\'s better than what they have at the moment.";
D.q[38] = "I\'m Graham Finame. Everybody around here knows me, and any monster that chanced upon my sharpened blade is now a dead monster. If you\'re interested, I\'m selling everything you need to become a blacksmith.";
D.q[103] = "Hey, buddy! I\'m retiring soon and so I\'m selling my Shovel Smith manual. If you\'re interested, I\'ll throw in a hammer for forging shovels. I can\'t even lift it anymore because of my degenerative osteoarthritis...*sigh*";
D.q[140] = "Fantastic, you sure are lucky! You won, and it\'s been a while since it last happened in this tavern.\n\n(Grizmine gives you the Kamas, scratching his whiskers and purring)";
D.q[199] = "Hey, hey, what\'s this... a player! If you can bring me back a five-leaf clover, I\'ll introduce you to Wiss Catz, the legendary Ecaflip who fell into a pot of clover-soup as a child.";
D.q[242] = "Oh really, you stick like a leech! Well, I can\'t stand to be alone here anymore. And I\'m afraid of the dark. Bring me 10 Tofu feathers and 2 Blue Jellies to make me some wings... I want to get out of here. I\'ll give you the key to my cave in exchange.";
D.q[259] = "Oh thanks! If you manage to get rid of those damned creatures, I\'ll make it worth your while.\nHey, wipe that look off your face, it won\'t be like that, but you\'ll get a decent enough reward.";
D.q[281] = "Haha! Do you really think I\'d reveal my diabolical plans to the first person who walks by? I\'ll only share them with a real criminal.\n(muttering) Pfff...It\'s so difficult to find qualified workers these days.";
D.q[283] = "Hi, my name is Simgood and I\'m a sailorman. I\'ve sailed the several seas, but now my dream is to open a souvenir shop and sell thousands - even millions - of souvenirs all over the world. People will fight over them just to say they have a memento of Simgood the Sailorman. I think I\'ll start with carving or painting crab claws.";
D.q[297] = "Hi, my name is Sel. Bellus Sel. I guard this cave. I only let experienced warriors in, those who are able to survive more than 20 seconds when faced with the terrible creature that haunts this place... Furthermore, I\'d like you to bring me four strands of Boar Hair and two of their Tusks. My son asked me to make him a mask but my work keeps me here all the time.";
D.q[341] = "Carvers use different species of wood according to their needs but sometimes, they also need other rare elements such as precious stones or metals.\nThe more you progress in your carving profession, the more powerful the items you carve will be. \nI can teach you some of the Carving professions, but I must warn you, learning a profession takes a long time and you\'ll have to practise a lot to improve your skills.";
D.q[366] = "Ah, I like your style! If you win, you\'ll get the whole pot!\nOtherwise, half of this amount will go towards the jackpot...";
D.q[370] = "Hi! I\'m Otho Laringo, the blacksmith. I\'m looking for an apprentice to help me make weapons.\nAll the ones I\'ve had so far ran away after half-a-day\'s work....Tsss they\'re all chickens! I need some important resources to make my weapons... Of course, I\'ll pay you.";
D.q[383] = "I need so many things that I made a list! So let\'s see...\n60 Arachnee Legs, 55 Five-Leaf Clovers, 40 Karne Rider nails and 15 Boowolf tails. \nI don\'t want to kill myself looking for all those things so I\'ll take everything in one go for a magic scroll.\n";
D.q[387] = "My motto is: Only give others what they already possess.\nIf you want me to make a scroll, bring me the ingredients, and the recipe of course...";
D.q[390] = "Hi, I\'m Koussein Trengon but I\'m no Duke of Koussein, not yet. I always trust my lucky star. It brings me everything I need. For example, I bet you it will soon bring me the ingredients I need to make a potion.";
D.q[400] = "Hi, let\'s make it simple, okay, just call me The Stallion. Yesterday, I ate some Dragon Pig Ham. It\'s well known and widely loved but in fact, it was a really bad idea. The results were not exactly what I hoped for... So, I need some ingredients to heal me.";
D.q[426] = "The Eniripsa class have a particular liking for wands. Much intelligence and a little wisdom are required to use them. Wands rarely cause serious damage but often give their holder incredible magic powers.\nWand carvers use a Wand Gasher.";
D.q[427] = "Bows are the favourite weapons of the Cras who prefer long-distance attacks. \nBows rarely cause serious damage but a critical hit can be really surprising. \nThey require agility and strength to be used.\nBow carvers use the Bow Gasher.";
D.q[429] = "Greetings, disciple, I\'m one of the six Rogue Masters. Vil Smisse is our Grand Master.\nIf you want to progress through the Order and obtain more authority, you\'ll have to carry out numerous quests and tasks in order to prove your merit.";
D.q[432] = "Bakers are respectable people whose bread and butter is making bread for butter... hehehe.\nWe bakers are respected because we provide bread to weakened adventurers that need to recover strength.\nWith experience a baker will cook more and better breads. The better the bread is, the more health it will restore.\nBakers use a Kneader to prepare bread dough.";
D.q[438] = "Ah, you know Hanniboul Smisse? He\'s our chief, he\'s in charge around here and he\'ll do whatever it takes to rescue me when crazy people take me for a crazy person and try to lock me up.\nI shouldn\'t be telling you this, though.";
D.q[442] = "This Treechnid is one of the oldest in the Province of Amakna. It has already killed most of my Lumberjack friends but worse than that, it killed my family one night while we were sleeping out in the open.\nIt happened deep in the forest I\'m the only one who survived...\nI want to take my revenge but I can\'t do it myself... That\'s why I\'m asking you to do it for me... Go and kill that monster and I\'ll reward you fairly.";
D.q[450] = "The famous Boots of Klime...\nIt\'s Lee Chainedarpenter, an illustrious but scatterbrained insomniac shoemaker, who tried to make the famous Powerful Boots of Klime one evening... No one knows how he did it. But the first specimens he made were eerily full of power. When he eventually realised what he had done, it was too late...";
D.q[459] = "Everything... I\'ve lost everything... The idea was good... I had all the books I needed to train apprentices...Some cloaks, some hats... They would have been ready for anything. \nAnd then, those damned Dark Blacksmiths came, they didn\'t spare me... They stole all my books! I\'m sure they hid them in their den...";
D.q[465] = "A vely good molning to you, my fliend! You look like you could do with some help, and I\'m youl fox! Hele\'s the lecipe of the potion you\'ll need to take if you want to ventule fulthel on this island.  A good alchemist\'s assistant should be able to plepale it fol you, if you ask. \nYou\'ll need 1 Jelly of each coloul: so 1 Blue, 1 Led and 1 Gleen. \nGood luck and may the Tail of the Gleat Fox be with you!";
D.q[478] = "Fowgive me my Wa but I didn\'t wecognize you.\nDoes youw majesty wish to entew the hall of the Dofus?";
D.q[494] = "I have to send him messages on a regular basis. If you deliver him this letter, I\'ll give you 1,000 Kamas and your reputation in our clan will grow..\nYou\'ll find him to the south of the dark forest of Amakna.";
D.q[496] = "Rogue masters all have a different part to play and a region to rule. There are 3 masters in Amakna.\nMy role is to train and accompany apprentices who want to join our clan.\n";
D.q[497] = "Hello, I see you have the possessions of the Wa... Accowding to ouw laws, the pewson appeawing in the Dofus Woom with the possessions of the Wa in his inventowy can take the Dofus. \nBut fow that, you\'ll have to give me what you have.";
D.q[530] = "Don\'t worry. Here are 2,000 Kamas to pay for the bread. I knew I\'d find something useful for you to do.";
D.q[552] = "Ah dear guest! What a great question!\nFirst, the eastern side of the island is a vast beach where you can bask and sunbathe. Tanned skin makes you look younger and less tired, and will make people jealous when you go back to work. Enjoy a few moments of relaxation on the sand and taste the wonderful Kokonuts which are always on hand.";
D.q[553] = "Pirates occupy the northern part of the island, and will welcome you with open arms. Don\'t forget to taste their 120 year-old rum, and introduce yourself to their illustrious Captain. Oh, and one last thing, never make fun of his lucky shorts. According to the legend, they brought him enough luck to escape the many storms he encountered when sailing on the Terrible Seas of Kalmar.";
D.q[558] = "Just one thing, mind you don\'t injure yourself on the pieces of wreckage scattered all over the beach. \nThrill seekers may want to go for a walk towards the southern part of the jungle - guaranteed frights with our local pirate ghosts. Don\'t be afraid, though, they\'re not that dangerous...";
D.q[560] = "I can propose you to go on a dream island, heaven on earth. Just imagine: lying down on the fine golden sand, your delicate skin getting tanned, the sea breeze on your face. In your hand, a Kokonut milk cocktail. Once you\'ve spent the whole day doing nothing at all, you\'ll meet your friends and sit at the locals\' table. They are skilled cooks and will treat you like a king. In the evening, just admire the magical show of the moon lightning the vast flora and fauna of the place. If you want to entertain yourself with some shivers, agents who have been especially trained for a century will be at your disposal.";
D.q[608] = "Hehehe, it was a good idea to come to this island. There are some valuable goods knocking around, not to mention all the weaklings with overflowing pockets... No need to fight, all you have to do is wait for a Kanniball or another local monster to gobble them up.";
D.q[635] = "If you\'re looking for recipes, you should go to the library. An alchemist created an encyclopedia composed of more than 12 books about rare recipes.";
D.q[641] = "To continue your formation, you must have a registered trainer. But I\'m not registered. Go to the southernmost island. There\'s an alchemist trainer in the area though I can\'t remember his name. Show him your scroll and the flower I gave you. \nIt will be proof that you\'ve completed your first lesson.";
D.q[711] = "Hello young adventurer! I\'m the fencing master of the Bonta Militia.\n\nIf you want to serve in the ranks of the militia, give me a hand to get some Twiggy Swords to train my guys. You\'ll have to go get me about ten swords in the Blacksmith\'s Quarters, in the East of the city.";
D.q[717] = "Hello little scaraleaf! I hope you don\'t have holes in your boots \'cause you\'ll need a good pair for this mission. I always have a beer at my colleague\'s tavern on the east side of the city. I usually take advantage of that moment of relaxation to exchange some special cards with him. He owes me one since we last meet. Could you go pick it up it for me?";
D.q[719] = "Apparently, Torche wasn\'t at his post the last time you challenged him. To come in useful for me, you should go round the Inns to bring me the list of the militiamen as bone idle as he is. \nTell them you\'re doing a census and that you must take their badges until this evening.";
D.q[740] = "My nephew Dike Tarak can often be found playing in the northern district. If you meet him, let him win. It will make him happy. And if he\'s happy, I\'m happy too... Get it?";
D.q[742] = "My nephew is so proud he defeated you, he really made me laugh.\nHowever, he told me that some friends of his were going to do some not so Bontarian things in the baker\'s district. I\'d like you to put together a little inspection and put things to rights!";
D.q[754] = "Do you know Lord Crow? I\'d like you to steal his scythe, so that I can check whether it cuts better than my sabre or not.\nWhat do you mean I\'m taking advantage of my authority? So what? Back to work #1!";
D.q[762] = "Ah #1 I was waiting for you! Tomorrow I must train my guys, but this sun will get in my eyes. I need you to find a nice, big Champo to keep me in the shade.";
D.q[821] = "To nail those Bontarians\' mouths shut once and for all, we\'re going to start practicing with hammers.\nThere\'s only one problem - we\'ve hardly any hammers... so bring me 10 Twiggy Hammers, or you and nine of your comrades won\'t be able to train.";
D.q[854] = "Our next plan is to corrupt an important Bontarian and to make him our ally... when the time is right. I want to find someone who is highly placed and who could be convinced to betray Bonta. You might find some clues around the tower of Bonta.";
D.q[965] = "The stones used for the fortifications of Bonta have been hewed out of remains of Cracklers of the Plains. \nA Bwork troop breached the northern fortifications last night.\nIf you want to give us a hand, bring me at least 4 stones of Cracklers of the Plains. This will help up rebuild the fortifications.";
D.q[983] = "Hi, my name is Ned Etsith, I\'m interested in odontostomatology. I bet you can\'t even pronounce that word, never mind understand what\'s involved. Now that\'s fascinating, isn\'t it?";
D.q[1007] = "What have you done to it? This necklace is completely mashed up!\nI can\'t give it back to the mayor\'s daughter in such a state! \nGo to the jeweller\'s district and work it out! I want a brand new necklace!\n";
D.q[1010] = "He told me there was some sort of similarity between a human and a Gobball tooth. That animal will ALWAYS surprise me... \nOnce you have the teeth, bring them to Ned in the south-west of the city.\nI hope you\'re educated enough to remember how many teeth a human being has.";
D.q[1011] = "You\'re on leave until tomorrow. Come back later for a new mission. \nI\'m in a good mood so take these 1,000 Kamas for your travelling costs... and to stand your round at the tavern...heh heh heh! But don\'t drink too much and stay fit, I\'ll need help again soon.";
D.q[1035] = "So you\'re Amayiro\'s new recruit?! You look very young, aha, if only you knew what was in store for you... You want the map, I suppose. I hope you have clean hands... If you don\'t want to be on the receiving end of one of Amayiro\'s grudges, I\'d advise you not to get any blood or dirt on the thing. As they say round here, \'Hell hath no fury like Amayiro\'s grudge\'. ";
D.q[1020] = "I bet some of them will be surprised when they get their next pay.\nThanks #1. I\'ll give them their badges back myself.";
D.q[1037] = "Hunting is quite easy! All you need is the right weapon to kill the animal straight away. If the animal is only hurt or badly wounded, the hunter won\'t get a good price for the meat afterwards.\n";
D.q[1056] = "What an example of obedience! You\'ll go far... that is, if I let you...\nWhat do you think of a little entertainment as a reward?";
D.q[1090] = "So, you had a nice break?\nI\'ve a hunch that you forgot to bring beer to your chief... for that you can go and get me one at the Kikim.\nOh, I almost forgot. The tavern is in Bonta, so good luck...\nJust capture a farmer and send him to get the beer for you! Ha-ha-ha!";
D.q[1102] = "Hello dear Customer. We make anything you can think of to measure - shirts, pieces of armour, throats, whatever you want as long as we can cut it with our knives... and as long as you can pay.";
D.q[1114] = "Mmm. I got shoooooees they\'re multiplying, and I\'m looooosiing control-ol!...\nNO THAT\'S NOT IT! Ooh...I\'m a big shot, not a singer! How will I manage to string two words together to charm her... Eh? hum, sorry I was thinking out loud...sorry...";
D.q[1141] = "What? What are you talking about? You think I\'m a beggar? Never... I only asked you for 5 Kamas.";
D.q[1142] = "Hm, that reminds me you\'re not old enough to drink Greedovore wine yet.\nWhat a pity, I won\' be able to share it with you.\nApparently have a letter for me...Well thank you... incompetent bloody... next time you\'ll end up in the dungeon, got it?!";
D.q[1147] = "Hm, I see... This is worse than I thought it would be...\nI\'ll write you my answer right away.";
D.q[1150] = "The delivery man made a mistake and gave me four times the amount of healing powder I asked for. To get rid of it quickly, I\'m selling it for 1,000 Kamas a pop. Special price, my friend, real special price.";
D.q[1160] = "Don\'t lose your composure when you see my enclosure! Oh, if only it were bigger!\nThe problem is, boar are like pigs. The older they get, the more stupid they become.\n\nBring me young wild boar, I\'ll buy them from you for a good price. You won\'t lose out on the deal, you have Robin Gaywould\'s word.";
D.q[1168] = "Alright, but you\'ll have to do me a favour before. Aga Dou has bait for me and I need it very quickly. \nHere\'s the deal: if you can bring the bait back here in less than 5 minutes, I\'ll teach you the tricks of the trade.";
D.q[1214] = "You can now join our lines.\nWhich Order do you wish to join? \nThe warriors of the Bleeding Heart Order, the healers of the Unsound Mind Order, or the Putrid Eye Order?\nBe careful, this choice is very important. You won\'t be able to change your mind once you\'ve chosen your order.";
D.q[1215] = "To join our Order, the very least you can do to show us your merit\'s to bring us 1 Crow\'s Eye.";
D.q[1217] = "To join our Order, the very least you can do to show us your merit\'s to bring us Bwork Magus Beard Hair.";
D.q[1245] = "Heya, I\'m the great Paro Cabanne, generous creator, astounding designer and clothes-prophet of genius. What can I do for you, my dear fellow?";
D.q[1250] = "You aren\'t the smartest, are you? To make pulp all you have to do is crush 4 different Blop flowers with a Munster Crusher!";
D.q[1275] = "Well #1, don\'t you want to do your teeth done up like new? It will only cost you 10,000 Kamas...\nMate\'s rates... because a friend in need is a friend indeed!";
D.q[1280] = "So, you\'re the one on fatigue this week, #1? Take some potatoes from the pile on the ground and peel them on the table at the back.\nOnce you have peeled 200 pods, bring them to me.";
D.q[1299] = "Hi #1, Amayiro can\'t stop singing your praises. That\'s the reason why I need your help.";
D.q[1312] = "Why are you offering me money you don\'t even have? Are you trying to make a fool of me? You\'re breaking one of the most important rules, never make a fool of someone stronger than you! I\'ll let you off this time, clear off!";
D.q[1328] = "What a pretty Champo! Knowing you, I was expecting something with holes in it. Ha ha!";
D.q[1388] = "A wizard just passed by. He was running way too fast for me to catch him. You can still stop him, he\'s travelling North-West.";
D.q[1393] = "I caught sight of a man dressed in a blue cloak, running north. Was he a Bontarian fugitive? If so, he picked the wrong way to go - he was heading straight for the Sidimote Gorge were our warriors patrol.";
D.q[1402] = "Here is the poison in question. Put the cake in his sideboard, he\'s used to having it delivered so he will certainly find it tomorrow morning.\nGood luck!";
D.q[1403] = "Are you really sure you don\'t want to obey an order of the steward of Bonta?";
D.q[1404] = "Ok, I\'ll find someone else to do this work.\nAnd don\'t you dare go and tell it around, or you\'ll undergo the same fate as Rimaraf!";
D.q[1415] = "Champos? Fungi Masters wear them. You can find them in the fields south of Bonta.\nIt\'s no use bringing me a Champo that\'s destined for use in combat, only the first one you find on a Fungi Master will do.";
D.q[1446] = "Another thrashing for a cowardly warrior then. What do ya want? A thrashing too? Humm, I\'m a bit tired today, you won\'t have the honour of fighting against me.";
D.q[1471] = "That\'s it? You came all the way to Bonta just for that? Oto wants you dead, or what? I\'d have sent it to him by kwak tomorrow as usual.\nAlright. Here it is. This way you didn\'t come for nothing. Off you go!";
D.q[1480] = "Eh, I hope you got the message. I always keep an eye on you, heheh... Ah, there\'s something else in your bag of eyes... A CLUSTER OF EGGS! Are you crazy?! Got an idea of what will happen if they hatch here... AARGH, TOO LATE! You\'ll pay for this!";
D.q[1491] = "I don\'t care about your shorts, you idiot! One of the cartel heads wants to see you, don\'t keep her waiting or I\'ll have the pleasure of killing you. She\'s inspecting the basement of the tower at the moment.";
D.q[1495] = "Well, I see... Really good, you managed to keep the secret of a superior. I\'m proud of you. Ok, I haven\'t got that much to give you for the moment... How about a little trip...or... yes, that\'s it. Let me explain... while I was on an expedition to a far-off island, I tasted a delightful little tipple called Greedovore Wine, try to bring me some of it and I\'ll give you a taste... I promise!";
D.q[1513] = "Oh, I see what you\'re talking about. My uncle brought me some brand new bows and told me that militiamen would come to collect them.\nHe also told me to sell them at 1,000 Kamas each... business is business as he says...\nJust remember they\'re very fragile - they break after one fight.";
D.q[1538] = "Hi #1! I\'ve decided to cook turtle brain tonight. But I can\'t go to Moon Island myself... Plus, if the brain isn\'t cooked within 5 minutes of the death of the beast, the dish is inedible...\nFortunately, you\'re here to give me a hand!";
D.q[1566] = "Hem, you seem clever... just tell Amayiro the matter is settled.\nHere, take the whole week\'s takings in exchange... that makes... 10,000 Kamas...";
D.q[1599] = "When you gain a level your character becomes a little more powerful. This way, you earn 5 points that you\'ll be able to share out among your features and 1 bonus point for you to boost your spells. I can show you how to use your feature points if you wish. If not, go straight to the next room. I\'ll show you how to develop your spells there.";
D.q[1601] = "One item is missing yet. You have to equip one necklace, one belt and one headband. Come back later when you have this 3 items.";
D.q[1617] = "(ne pas traduire)";
D.q[1621] = "Hi, what brings you to the cloud city?\nMy friend and I are making potions that will help us move faster than a tornado! But don\'t say a word about this to Girle Pylote... she only believes in mechanical devices... ";
D.q[1629] = "Thank you! As my mother used to say: If you eat some Redjely and Greenjely, never eat 4 Bluejely at the same time!";
D.q[1631] = "Thank you! As my mother used to say: If you eat some Blujely and Greenjely, never eat 2 Redjely at the same time!";
D.q[1632] = "How are you, #1? It\'s far too cold to go for a walk in Amakna.\nOh, I met someone this morning who asked me to give you his regards... argh, I can\'t remember his name... help me... he\'s the classiest Enutrof in the country, you know who I mean? I\'m sure you do. Really, you don\'t? Never mind...";
D.q[1640] = "#1, I was waiting for you. I already know the question you want to ask me, you\'re so predictable...\n\nI also know that you were about to forget to give me the 100 Kamas you must pay to ask me a question, so I think I\'ll remind you of it right now.";
D.q[1678] = "It\'s easy! Tofus will appear randomly on the playing board and vanish just as quick. The goal is to smash the Tofus before they disappear. But be careful! You must only hit YELLOW Tofus, if you hit an ORANGE Tofu, you lose!\nIf you manage to hit 60 Tofus without making a mistake, the big prize is yours.";
D.q[1686] = "Welcome to the Trool Fair!\nThe entrance fee for adults is 10 Kamas and it\'s free for any child who can pass under Iop\'s sword!\nBe careful! Tickets are only valid for 24 hours...";
D.q[1711] = "The Sacrier temple is located northward of the village of Amakna. Talk to Rihine Plehouverte to continue your training.";
D.q[1713] = "Hello #1! I can see that my brothers have started your training. But you still have a lot to learn. Before you venture through the region, I\'ve a challenge for you.";
D.q[1721] = "Fecas can use any weapon, but they handle staffs and wands best.";
D.q[1746] = "Eniripsas are very intelligent characters but they\'re always looking for things to help them become smarter.";
D.q[1773] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Sram. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[1785] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[1791] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Cra temple.\nIt will cost you a Silk String.";
D.q[1794] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Ecaflip temple.\nIt will cost you a Five-Leaf Clover.";
D.q[1815] = "Heltan, the blacksmith of our temple, disappeared in a time rift, and my Dopples refuse to fight if they don\'t have a little twiggy hammer for each combat... \nIf you want to fight one, you\'ll have to bring one of these hammers, until we find Faurge Heltan...";
D.q[1817] = "Amine wants some Plissken skins to decorate the temple, and once again he asked me to demand you some... There are days like this when Amine dreams about creating pyramidal temples or writing with strange pictograms, it\'s best not to try to know why...";
D.q[1826] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sram temple.\nIt will cost you Boar Leather.";
D.q[1827] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sram temple.\nIt will cost you Gobball leather.";
D.q[1833] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sadida temple.\nIt will cost you an Ambusher leaf.";
D.q[1849] = "*You suddenly understand why... it\'s the pink Bow Meowette over there! \nBut what can you do to draw her attention to him? You need to find something to make her notice him.";
D.q[1863] = "That suits you reeaall good. Yes, that gives me goosebumps, I swear. You\'re going to seduce all the women around with that! But don\'t hesitate changing though. Tailors can do many creations to make you a unique style!";
D.q[1880] = "He has the muscles like the warts on a fly\'s pee-pee... brain not bigger! Hahahah... An here you go interrupt mine game! I moved it! I put it in garden to stop the Bow Wow fighting it.";
D.q[1882] = "Blimey, thank you! I get so involved in my work that I often forget where I live, ha, ha! I can see that you\'re a helpful soul - that can get you killed around here, kid! Anyway, would you mind finding an evil dandelion for me? I often see some hanging around the fields North East of the village...\nI\'d like to compare their seeds with the Epyss Grains I collected yesterday.";
D.q[1899] = "A bear, is it? If you\'re looking to track it down, I saw it roaming West of here last night. Thanks for taking the trouble, you\'ll be justly rewarded!";
D.q[1904] = "Find, select and buy the finest flours from the farmers. Make the dough, knead it and bake it: that\'s all you have to know to become a baker. It seems simple, but each step must be carefully done and requires specific skills. That\'s why so many types of bread exist.";
D.q[1915] = "At the end of the day, all the new recruits were rather sluggish. I think I should hire highly motivated workers from day to day. There are loads of applicants for this kind of job. If you like, you can make the first delivery of the day for me, you\'ll get paid double just for today. Then you can make a second delivery whenever you want.";
D.q[1916] = "Our wheat cellar is filled with gravel, I can\'t wait for the Enutrofs to clear everything away so I can feed my Gobballs... If I can\'t have wheat, beer will have to do...\nWould you mind getting me some? I need 5 beers, so I\'ll give you 10 Kamas. Just take the cheapest kind, the furry little creatures prefer quantity over quality!";
D.q[1919] = "Creating jewellery requires true abilities and never-failing patience. It also demands a great artistic sense... alas, I\'ll never be as gifted as Azra lazarus from the village of Amakna...";
D.q[1936] = "Arrrgh! My \'ead iz gilling me... as if I \'ad been drampled on by a \'erd ov Treechnids...";
D.q[1951] = "Thank you, thank you, thank you! Oh man, I\'m so busy right now. Hey, can you ask the butcher to kill the Gobball I brought him. I\'m not a killer, you know... I gotta say, though, I love that black pudding stew! I just try not to think where it comes from, you know! Could you buy 2 lemons from Seth Sourcet, too? Here, take 5 more Kamas for that.";
D.q[1964] = "Ha, you don\'t muck about, do you! Well, not many people are allowed to see the boss except maybe a high-ranking soldier now and again.\nListen, if it\'s what you really want, I\'ll cut you a deal. Give me 2,500 Kamas and that torn cloak you have there, and we\'ll see - unless you want to take us all on at once!";
D.q[1970] = "Who do you think you\'re? I\'m gonna... Hmmm. Wait, you told me that the Innkeeper is betting his life on this beer... Interesting... We will stop stealing his beer if he agrees to sell some to us at a really low price. Convince him if he hesitates! Off you go!";
D.q[1985] = "Ok, here\'s what you\'re going to do: Go and see Touh Flowa, a Sadida friend. He\'ll give you a Dizbi flower. But for the essence, you\'ll need the help of Dragonsly, one of my previous student, who\'s now an Alchemist. Give me your map, I\'ll show you where Touh Flowa is located. Your compass will guide you.\nGood luck.";
D.q[1987] = "There\'s something missing for me to speak to you Eniripsa to Eniripsa...oh, right, you\'re not an Eniripsa.";
D.q[1991] = "Our Enutrof friends are in trouble. They have discovered things... that have disturbing repercussions. You\'ll find a search party in the tunnels of the town, but don\'t go there alone! It\'s not safe. Tell me what you find. And good Luck!";
D.q[1996] = "Hey! Wazzza? Want a piece of my new invention? With this stuff you don\'t need your wings to get high anymore. But by the way, why did you come here?";
D.q[2001] = "I\'m trying to get my employees to work longer and hard... nothing seems to do it. Orders are still coming in fast and I\'m damned if I\'m gonna waste money taking on more permanent workers!\nSay, if you want to earn a few Kamas yourself, I\'ll need some Pizznosh delivered around the city sometime soon. ";
D.q[2035] = "I heard that an Enutrof from the building site has been turned into a dark miner down in the underpasses! This poor miner did not change his old habits, though... he still swallows his share of tipple down at the inn. You must bring a drop of his blood to Dragonsly, the alchemist. He\'ll know what to do with it. But first of all, go and talk to Dragonsly. He\'ll give you a syringe. Use it to extract the blood once you\'ve overcome the dark miner. I\'ve shown you where you can find Dragonsly, just follow your compass! And keep me up to speed...";
D.q[2039] = "You\'re back! Very well, show it to me! Excellent. Now, to assemble everything... There! A beautiful sword, quite plain, but a warrior shouldn\'t be judged by a sword alone! Go and see your master again, he will teach you how to handle it. Good luck, and watch your fingers!";
D.q[2045] = "Don\'t look at me like that! You have to try to learn on your own! Go and see Joe Stonefiddler, the Master of the Enutrof Guild, and offer your services... 4 or 5 good shovel strokes and you\'ll be in great shape...\nWoah, infiltration, spying... You\'ll have a Sram\'s life! Come back to me quickly.";
D.q[2049] = "I see you have no weapon. Here, please take this purse, with my compliments as an elder Ecaflip. With the contents, you should be able to afford one. I think Kwartzwatch might have played a trick on me, though - the metal might disappear soon if no one takes it!";
D.q[2050] = "Ah! You\'ve got the Dark Miner\'s blood? Good, I\'m going to analyse it. I\'ll send the results of my tests to your master.";
D.q[2061] = "Back again, then! Show me your sword... Holy moly, that\'s beautifully done! I\'ll do you the honour of etching the Ecaflip insignia on it... you\'re one of us now! But I still don\'t know what those Enutrofs are up to. I\'d bet my paws there\'s gold involved! What about christening that sword of yours down in the underpasses? Be very careful: don\'t risk your life!";
D.q[2070] = "Yeah! Are you here for the staff? Of course you\'re here for the staff... Okay, I\'m going to make it with the Hurrywood you brought me! Hum, I think this is how it\'s done... a bit on the right, a bit on the left... *doubts*... and a bit in the middle too... I th... no! I\'m sure of it! Here you go, and it\'s... oh right, the magic words!...ahoummmm telagen hoo en wat doo nut no!...done!";
D.q[2077] = "Hm! You think I\'m a pain, don\'t you! I probably have a little bit of Hurrywood left. There you go, but careful now, a rare thing it is!";
D.q[2085] = "Oh noo! Sacred Nepra! I \'ave never see someone so angry! She\'s like zat... but she have a good \'eart.. . Zank you! I owe you one!";
D.q[2090] = "Hello there, young Feca. My name is Fallanster. My daughter, Allisteria, told me about all the things you\'ve done. She didn\'t have time to bring you a bowl of our Gobball black pudding stew, it was all gone in a flash!";
D.q[2100] = "Haha, I knew someone as smart as you would jump at the chance.\nOkay, listen up... It\'s easy. You have exactly 10 minutes to deliver this to Erty Trapchet. He\'ll be in the park in the centre of the city. If you\'re too slow, you\'ll have to pay for the pizznosh yourself! HA! Get out of here.";
D.q[2108] = "Saketsu told me you\'d come. Thanks a lot! Let\'s see what this drop of blood can tell us. Well, of course it\'s just a figure of speech! After a few tests, I\'ll know which illness struck him!";
D.q[2134] = "Do you bring me what I need for the lining? I need 5 balls of Gobball wool and the cloak I made for you.";
D.q[2137] = "If you carry on forgetting things like that, Joe will send you deep inside the earth for a date with the Tofus of the Osamodas! Come on! Faster! Go and see Clyde Peus of the Feca guild for me!";
D.q[2151] = "Go and see Dragonsly, the alchemist. He\'ll melt down those Kamas and make you a good blade. I told you the way. Just follow your compass now.";
D.q[2167] = "Well, now that you have your own sword, put on your equipment, go and kill two Arachnees! Thus you\'ll show me what you can do. If you prove yourself worthy of it, I\'ll entrust you with a more important mission.";
D.q[2217] = "Well... \'was within an inch of death and you speak \'bout minerals? Well, ore, metals, there\'s nothing more beautiful to a miner! In the hands of a good alchemist, they\'ll become potions, in the hands of a dagger forger, they\'ll become swords... And \'will sure need swords, betcha!";
D.q[2222] = "What are you waiting for to bring the remedy to the Enutrofs?";
D.q[2226] = "Woah, what do you want me to do with that bow? Do I look like an archer to you?";
D.q[2261] = "Creating a group will allow you to communicate easily and rapidly with the adventurers you\'ll have gathered during a game.\nBut you have to distinguish a group from a guild. A group is temporary. The guild is permanent and is subject to conditions.";
D.q[2263] = "Hey! Hello... hi! How are you? Good... good. That\'s great. I was just thinking, you know, like, whyyyy... do people have so many different types of hair?\nI\'ve counted, like, eleven types of hair in the world. I was actually needing to get all the hair together to have a... oh my god... could you, like, maybe... if I give you a list could you, like, bring me back one strand of each type? ";
D.q[2273] = "Baaah... life is tough down here. Yeaaah yeah...And if a creature grinds down your vitality all the way, you\'ll bite the dust. You\'ll have to sit down to recover. Eat the bread from a bakery, drink a healing potion - some alchemists make excellent ones - and you\'ll make the most out of life, if you have any left.....";
D.q[2274] = "Rumours, yeaaaaah... It\'s the talk of Astrub now... But don\'t trust the faces of the creatures you see... If you\'re alone and not too experienced, don\'t try to annoy the old Gobball, ok! These creatures will tear the skin off your backside like a tuft of grass and chew it up... Yeah...*Woan Aye looks pensive*";
D.q[2281] = "Each being that treads this worldly stage should take time to find his god, and go to the right temple to honour the celestial master.";
D.q[2301] = "Dragonsly, the Alchemist, should be able to get a good Dizbi flower tea going. It\'s great, you\'ll see...";
D.q[2318] = "We make good sandwiches with Arachnee legs... You\'re not too picky are you? I advise you to carry some with you if you want to survive! They\'re, ehh, they\'re... They\'re very high in protein I\'m told. Ah, before I forget, I need some more - see how popular they\'re! Can you bring me 10 legs please?... That should be enough for the moment.";
D.q[2322] = "Eniripsas told me there are no \'infectious aged-aunts\' in the sick Tofus feathers... I didn\'t really get it but something tells me there\'s nothing to be scared about. Eniripsas could be interested in Tofus eggs...and I could too, hahaha! So... let\'s say... 10 Tofus eggs. That should do for now.";
D.q[2331] = "There are several important rules to keep in mind when selling objects.\n\nTo sell objects in a marketplace, you have to choose the price and the quantity of objects you want to sell.\nBut be careful because you\'ll have to pay a tax when you put your objects on sale.\nYou won\'t get your tax back after the object has been sold or if you choose to take it back before it\'s sold.";
D.q[2339] = "Ahhh, yes indeed, this is Osamodas\' s manuscript for the bear invocation! Thank you for returning it to us!\nYou can tell Don Eaddat that the Gobball slaughter is over!";
D.q[2359] = "Hunting isn\'t that easy! You need a good weapon to kill the animal straight away. If the animal is only wounded or badly killed, you won\'t be able to get the good pieces of meat, which will get you a good price at the market.";
D.q[2365] = "That\'s Amakna over there. I tell ya, some weird things been happenin\' over that way. Maybe you\'d enjoy that, though, right?";
D.q[2373] = "Old legends! Don\' let that mess with \'head like the others! \'Don\' know half what I know, and \'making all that fuss about finding eggs...Rrrr kof kof *chesty cough*";
D.q[2374] = "Hum... The World of Eleven is changin\', yup. So, you want the Dofus? You should first charm the guardians, or fight them... Powerful guys those guardians... and jealous... Only experienced adventurers able are to take them on!";
D.q[2384] = "Are you sure you want to start a career as a Shovel smith?";
D.q[2391] = "Hello my friend! You must have the fisherman\'s fever as well if you\'ve come all this way to see me! Or maybe you just want to talk about the divine mysteries of the apendicidal coccyx?";
D.q[2393] = "Well, you\'re now my apprentice. You\'ll start with small creations, I\'ve drawn designs for them in your notebook. You\'ll also need some specially designed slashers for what you\'re going to sculpt. I sell many different kinds if you want to get one. Try to pick up the right slasher! Once you get it, you can use our work benches for sculpting.";
D.q[2401] = "Are you sure you want to spend days on end in the darkness, chipping away at a wall of rock? Being a miner is a vocation, you know that, don\'t you?";
D.q[2411] = "Hi, I\'m just a young apprentice... If you want to know more about our art, go and see Two-Fingers. He\'s spent all his time in the marketplace since it opened not so long ago.";
D.q[2413] = "Professions are divided into two main categories: harvesting and local crafts. Neither category could flourish without the other.\nFarmers, lumberjacks, fishermen, hunters and miners harvest raw materials from nature\'s bounty.\nThe local craftspeople, including all smiths, sculptors, jewellers, shoemakers and tailors use their skill to refine and craft these materials. \nAlchemy occupies a special place, as its practitioners are both harvesters and crafters at once.";
D.q[2414] = "Harvesters pass their days outdoors, reaping, chopping, digging and sometimes wildly kicking raw materials when they have ripened. Miners scratch at the mineral veins deep inside the earth while alchemists expertly select the finest and most potent flowers in the forests and fields. These raw materials, after a certain amount of refinement, from wheat to flour for instance, are ready to be sold! Craftspeople in particular are always ready to hand over a few Kamas for their wares...";
D.q[2421] = "What do woodcutters do? They cut down trees. What do they do with this wood? Well, that\'s more interesting. Between carvers carving bows, arrows and staffs, blacksmiths forging wooden-hilted swords and all the other uses wood can be put too, you\'ll never be short of eager customers. I must tell you that it\'s long hard work, however.";
D.q[2440] = "The fishmonger prepares the fish the fisherman catches. He cooks it, adds some spices... and voila, a tasty and nourishing dish, low in calories, high in... good stuff. According to my Auntie Peuh, it can even make you smart. Imagine that.";
D.q[2462] = "Hello you! If you like the sweet, sensual feel of a long, hard bit of wood as much as I do, go and see Oli Venders, the best lumberjack in Astrub. If you get on well, he may even take the time to teach you the basics of his profession. Follow the little pin on your compass.";
D.q[2467] = "Hello friend!\nIf you can feel your blood boiling in your veins as I can, I strongly advise you to go and see Saketsu. He\'s the master of our class. He will show you the path you must take. I can tell you where to find him, if you wish. Just follow your compass. Be careful, though, it\'s not a pretty scene in there!";
D.q[2469] = "You\'re a quick learner, young #1. I think you can now go back to the city of Astrub. No wait! I forgot! Keep in mind that this world is full of adventurers like you. Don\'t hesitate to talk to them by using your communication zone (on the bottom left). Some of them will ask for help, some others will help you and you\'ll even find some people who will offer you some quests to do. Have a look around the statue, you\'ll spot them easily...";
D.q[2471] = "Oh, alright. If you really want to prove yourself, go and see Ant Emicheun. His business is going through a bad patch...*sigh*. If you can help him, you\'ll probably be able to help me afterwards... once you\'re a bit stronger...";
D.q[2478] = "I\'ve heard that on Pandala island, there\'s a drink they make out of blue larvae fermented in Gobball saliva... they say it\'s quite tasty! First thing I\'ll do when I get there is try it out. Upon my word! But... we still don\'t know where Toyo Dzink is. If he doesn\'t come back with some amber, this bridge won\'t get fixed any time soon!";
D.q[2484] = "Are you looking for some Amber around here? I think you should go south of Amakna to find some, close to the forest.";
D.q[2504] = "Perfect! Wear this Pandawa hat to show you\'ve paid the tax! Now, I recommend you go visit Shaman Surivitna. What an odd noise! It\'s coming from your belly, isn\'t it? That\'s what happens when you wear a Pandawa hat in Pandala without being a Pandawa from Pandala... you get a visit from McSheth...";
D.q[2511] = "Helllloo! I\'m Pyrite! Underpasses in Astrub! The grossewer rat! Yep! We owe you our lives! Anyway, I heard your conversation with the Shaman - a nice Pandawa that one - you should go see Grandapan. He\'s the one who rules everything round here. If you\'re looking for the Dofus, and I believe this is the case, go see him he\'ll have some interesting things to tell you.";
D.q[2517] = "From now on, everyone can come and see the Dofus receptacle! Many people want to visit it - and they all buy souvenirs from our island! *Rubbing his hands.* Thank god for Grandapan! Mmh... How may I help you?";
D.q[2518] = "...This legend about dragon eggs is like a licence to print money! Our coffers will soon be overflowing! Mmh... Do you need anything?";
D.q[2536] = "Grandapan knows a lot of things! The Dofus receptacle is a genuine relic passed down by our ancestors... but don\'t tell me that\'s all you\'ve seen. Doesn\'t it prove the truth of the legend? Go ahead and have a look. It will definitely convince you. Oh! Have you felt the wisdom that shoots through your body when you look at the ancient statue of our goddess? You must see it as soon as possible!";
D.q[2543] = "If you come flask in hand, I shall protect you \'till the end, this is an Akwadala saying... it seems you recognise it! Let me taste this brew... Yuk! It\'s water! Water in a Pandapiler flask! SACRILEGE! I ought to chop your head off!";
D.q[2548] = "But well... Let\'s change the subject! Wise old Lenald liked the trick you played on the Master of Akwadala... Tell him to go to Waewdala and have some fun with the chief... unless it was Tewwdala, I didn\'t quite understand his accent... In any case, take care of yourself!";
D.q[2558] = "Don\'t deny the obvious! I know you brought one of those damned Dofus onto our island! We saw you going out of the Shaman\'s house! You broke the Pandikaze rule n°1: No Dofus on Pandala. I sentence you to ingest Pandweiser until you die! You\'ll be executed tomorrow. Imprison him, and good night!";
D.q[2563] = "Yes! The Dofus used to be watched by dwagons... But Histowy took cawe to scattew them in the fouw cownews of the World. They awe now in hands of cweatures who feaw neither God nor man, cwazy and destwuctive... Long ago, the Dofus carried a hawmonious auwa ovew the world. Now, this time is past.";
D.q[2572] = "The Dofus used to be wawded by dwagons... But Histowy took cawe to scattew them in the fouw cowners of the Wowld. They awe now in the hands of cweatures feawing neither God nor man, cwazy and destwuctive... Long ago, the Dofus wewe cawwying an hawmonious auwa ovew the wowld. Now, this time is wevolved...";
D.q[2576] = "You undelstood: the Dofus nevel left Pandala... All this time, it\'s been on this island. A white Dofus, still immaculate, that no one had touched fol ages... I hid it inside the dungeon on the peninsula, nolth-east of Pandala. And the Pandikazes, those gangstels, sabotaged the blidge... When I saw Dalk Vlad had a Dofus, I thought he had stolen that one.";
D.q[2588] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
