D.q[2607] = "Are you saying this underpass leads to the lair of some awful creature?\nHumm, now I understand the meaning of this huge skull on my manuscript. Hmm, let\'s see... so... the next one is to the north of the village. Just head for the Treechnid Forest, and you can\'t miss it... I\'m sure you\'re dying to have another go...";
D.q[2621] = "Groofff\n*He rolls around on the ground to amuse you.*";
D.q[2638] = "WHAT? BREAK UP MY MARRIAGE? TO MARRY WHO?!\nListen to me carefully, you little McSheth skidmark... NO WAY! Over my dead body!";
D.q[2656] = "If you go visit the master of Pandasiman, he\'ll show you how to use it best. He should be in the Dojo.";
D.q[2661] = "The Divine Clock has a life of its own and stabilizes itself in spite of the magical interference of the World and the Universe. When their influence becomes too great, it can happen that the doors of Time open slightly... at least enough for the terrifying monsters we call The demons of the Hours to escape into our World.\nThe agitation created around the Dofus lately, provokes greater and greater time fluctuations. You can guess the rest...";
D.q[2681] = "Hola! Do you like this sweet fermented bamboo perfume?! We\'ll get on well then... What do you want?";
D.q[2704] = "I said: Filst bling the Pandapiler to my old fliend, the Chief of the village of Akwadala";
D.q[2721] = "Everyone says those paths are twisting and the creatures that haunt them are not what you\'d call friendly. But a fellow by the name of Wally Elconom succeeded in drawing a map. It could be useful for you to meet him. He\'s often to be seen round Amakna.";
